3 March 2020 The determination of specimen Ox0233 as Cheilosia pagana was incorrect (tubes FS02358265 and FS02358320). I have re-determined the specimen as actually being: Cheilosia soror. NCBI taxon ID= 368781.Is there a mechanism in place within the SOPs to allow for specimens redetermination? This may also be relevant for taxonomy changes and description/splitting of species concepts in the future - something which isconstantly happening. June 2020, changed to idCheSoro1 from idChePaga1. Public name changed to idCheSoro1 on advice of Kerstin Howe on 26/10/20.
data.TAXON_REMARKS: Re-determined from C. pagana to C. soror
